modules.description: Handles HTTP request routing with pattern matching on URL paths and methods, supporting dynamic segments and middleware chaining. Operates on strings, lists, and custom route definitions structured as tuples. Used to define RESTful endpoints and manage request dispatch in web servers.

This module provides route construction, parsing, and matching operations for HTTP requests, leveraging a radix trie for efficient pattern matching. It works with typed representations of routes, request targets, and arguments, enabling extraction of OCaml values like integers, strings, and booleans from path segments and query parameters. Use cases include building web applications with structured, type-safe routing where dynamic segments and query parameters need precise validation and transformation.
